---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro"

const title = "Privacy | Wonder Tinker"
const description = "Privacy posture for the static Wonder Tinker site."
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} canonicalPath="/privacy/">
  <main id="main" class="site-shell page-stack">
    <article class="page-layout">
      <header class="page-header">
        <p class="eyebrow">Privacy</p>
        <h1>Privacy</h1>
        <p class="lede">
          Wonder Tinker is a static GitHub Pages site. No analytics package, tracking
          script, tracking pixel, comments system, account flow, payment flow, or
          newsletter backend is installed by default.
        </p>
      </header>
      <div class="prose">
        <h2>What the site collects</h2>
        <p>
          This repository does not add application code that collects visitor names,
          email addresses, cookies, local storage identifiers, or browser fingerprints.
          Reading a page does not create an account, subscribe the visitor, or send data
          to a project-owned backend.
        </p>
        <p>
          GitHub Pages or a visitor's network provider may keep standard delivery logs
          outside this repository. Wonder Tinker does not control those platform logs
          from site code.
        </p>

        <h2>Analytics and tracking</h2>
        <p>
          No analytics package is installed by default. No tracking script, tracking
          pixel, tag manager, advertising SDK, or session replay script is included by
          default.
        </p>
        <p>
          Search Console-style ownership verification may be added later because it
          does not require visitor tracking script code. If a visitor-measurement tool
          is added, this page must be updated first with the tool name, data collected,
          opt-out behavior, and removal instructions.
        </p>

        <h2>Content privacy</h2>
        <p>
          Posts must not publish secrets, API keys, private prompts, credentials, raw
          private logs, or personal data. AI model notes are limited to model name,
          model role, and human review boundary.
        </p>

        <h2>Future custom domain</h2>
        <p>
          A future custom-domain change must configure GitHub Pages DNS, add
          <code>public/CNAME</code>, update Astro <code>site</code> and canonical URL
          assumptions, rebuild the site, and confirm again that no analytics or
          tracking script was added during the domain change.
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
